id_table_1.caption: 7 reasoning skills with example for pre-training ReasTAP. Variable names indicate permissible instantiations. col denotes a column name, val denotes a cell value, and indices denote that a cell value must originate from the specified column. OPERATOR and ORDINAL correspond to operators and ordinal numeral that are instantiated according to the specific reasoning skill, e.g., for â€˜Temporal Comparisonâ€™, ORDINAL is replaced with a reasonable ordinal numeral such as "4th". And CONDITION:i can be 1) a cell value from the i-th column, or 2) number/temporal comparison statement (e.g. "later than 1967") if the i-th column is of number or date type.
